V). In this context, V represents the variance–covariance matrix of bxy, which includes the LD correlation between the IVs [17]. Using the HEIDI (heterogeneity in dependent instruments) outlier filtering [17], we crucially removed horizontal pleiotropic variants to avoid any possible violation of the MR assumptions outlined above (e.g. [25]). The fundamental concept was to test every IV for a significant deviation (di) of the individual bxy(i) from a target SNP that had a strong association with the exposure tested (bxy(top)).
